3 weeks ago (edited)
Fingernails copied their idea from the Webtoon LUFF by Arechan. The story has 93.4M Reads on Webtoon and 1.2M Subscriptions! With a Web comic that significant, it's hard to imagine no one in production was aware of this. American TV and Cinema keeps doing this and not giving credit. At least South Korean Productions will say, "From a popular webtoon" or list the webtoon. This film literally has the same exact premise. People use a scientifically developed system to discover their biological love match, and the main character discovers she has two. The story is about her finding out what love really means. Like C'mon... I like all the actors in this, and I don't blame them. But I do wonder who in the chain of command decided to plagiarize an original idea and not give credit during the creation of this film.
